 <purpose>
	 This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of the data that is used to detail how an activity is to be performed. The Activity method implementation application module supports the requirement to link the method for an activity 
to one or more detailed specifications of the method. The means to define the specifications are defined
in other modules:
<ul>
<li>Task specification;</li>
<li>Scheme.</li>
</ul>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
<li>the link between activity method and method specifications.</li>
 </inscope>

